# Part 2 — Describe your favourite city that you have visited.

One of my favourite cities that I’ve ever visited is Shanghai, which is located on the eastern coast of China. It’s one of the most modern and international cities in the country. I first learned about Shanghai when I was a child because I often saw it in movies, TV dramas, and travel videos online. Many people described it as a city full of opportunities, advanced technology, and impressive architecture, so I had always wanted to visit it someday.

I finally visited Shanghai during my summer vacation last year with a few of my university friends. We stayed there for about four days. During the trip, we visited many famous attractions, such as the Bund, Nanjing Road, and the Oriental Pearl Tower. What impressed me most was the skyline at night. When all the buildings lit up, the whole city looked futuristic and incredibly vibrant. I remember standing by the Huangpu River and feeling amazed by how modern and energetic the city was.

Another reason why I love Shanghai is the convenience of life there. The public transportation system is extremely efficient, especially the subway network. We could basically travel anywhere very quickly. Besides that, there were countless restaurants, cafés, bookstores, and shopping centers, which made the city feel lively all the time.

As a computer science student who is interested in AI and technology, I also admire Shanghai because it has many innovative companies and a strong technological atmosphere. I feel that people there are ambitious and open-minded, which really motivated me to work harder for my future career.

Overall, Shanghai is my favourite city because it perfectly combines modern development, cultural diversity, and exciting city life. I would definitely like to visit it again, and maybe even work there in the future.

